      <BlogCrossLinks title="Scrabble Words With Gh" />
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With GH — Silent & Sounding Digraph Guide</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">GH is one of English's most versatile digraphs — sometimes silent (KNIGHT, THOUGHT), sometimes a hard G (GHOST, GHEE). In Scrabble, G (2pts) + H (4pts) gives 6 base points from just two tiles. GH words tend to be long and common, making them bingo-friendly while still scoring well on shorter plays.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">GH Base Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">G=2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">+ H=4</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3 G-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2 H-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In Bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top GH Words by Score</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 KNIGHT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 points · 6 letters · Silent K+GH combo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 FREIGHT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 points · 7 letters · Bingo eligible</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ GHASTLY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 points · 7 letters · Hard G start</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ THROUGH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · 7 letters · Common word</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">GH Patterns to Memorise</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Pattern Recognition</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Most GH words fall into three families: <span class="text-white font-medium">-IGHT</span> (LIGHT, MIGHT, FIGHT, SIGHT), <span class="text-white font-medium">-OUGH</span> (THOUGH, DOUGH, ROUGH), and <span class="text-white font-medium">GH-starters</span> (GHOST, GHEE, GHAT). Learn these three patterns and you cover 80% of GH opportunities.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GHEE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GHOST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GHOUL</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LIGHT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FIGHT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">H on premium squares:</span> H is your 4-point tile — place it on DLS for 8 points from a single tile. In -IGHT words, H often lands mid-word where premium squares cluster.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">GHEE for tight spots:</span> This 4-letter word (8pts) fits in cramped board positions and uses the G+H together at the front. It's also hookable — GHEES adds an S for parallel plays.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo with -IGHT:</span> FIGHTING, LIGHTING, and KNIGHTLY are all 8+ letter bingo words using the -IGHT pattern. Hold I+G+H+T and look for the remaining tiles to complete.</p></div>
      </div>

